caption: Great neighborhood breakfast spot with the all american classics - eggs, sausages, bacon, toast etc. Some of the dishes they put a bit of a korean twist on it - you'll find some dishes with bulgogi in it. Definitely gonna be back for some more!
SO glad I found this place while googling the area for breakfast! Literally digging into their generously-portioned Locomoco now and it is INSANE. 🤯😋 Do yourself a favor and get some.
Simply the best! Only take out now, but does not skimp on serving👍🏾👍🏾👍🏾
doooooood! 💣💥 i had the spicy scrambler w/ grits and english muffin
Ordered breakfast for takeout. Loco moco is the best I've found in Oakland. The Korean pork omelet was also really unique and tasty. French toast and waffle were plentiful and fluffy.
I been loving this place every since i been little still do n the food is still bomb
Not sure how much this place paid for its positive reviews, but I feel like it was a lot. Drip coffee only, 8$ for 2 eggs (cheapest food item) and no milk (half and half only)
Delicious!!!!
1st time. Great service better food. I'll be back!!
The perfect hole in the wall/greasy spoon eatery for breakfast or lunch. Delicious fare and top notch service keeps me coming back time after time.

Great little breakfast/lunch spot. And I do mean LITTLE. A few small tables inside to compliment the maybe 7 or 8 counter stools, plus a couple of tables outside. A favorite breakfast spot among the locals.
Good morning breakfast
Friendly staff, great food. Their bacon is always cooked perfectly!
Great food
Cozy spot to grab a coffee and some delicious breakfast.
Tasty breakfast bulgogi n grits ! Pancake good! Nicely redone inferior .theres literally 50 hot suace to try... although the bulgogi allready has flavor!
Amazing food. It’s like they know exactly how I like my breakfast prepared down to the quality of the coffee. Really impressed! I’ll be back!

One of our favorite breakfast spots. They have the breakfast staples, but I particularly like Q's dishes. Q draws on korean cuisine, leading to dishes like eggs and bulgolgi with a choice between hash browns and rice. My favorite is the Qs …
Amazing what they've done with a small space. Food  and service are both excellent!!
(Translated by Google) I love food And attention is very good I recommend it 😊  (Original) Me encanta la comida Y la atención es muy buena Te lo recomiendo 😊
Omg it's such a little nondescript little hole in the wall but the food is incredible. I would have never thought to go in here and have breakfast but I decided to on a whim and I'm so happy I did.

Found this little gem after getting off work! The bulgogi omelette is amazing! Definitely getting it the next time I’m getting off work! Very small place opens from Monday to Saturday 7 am- 2 pm! Love the food, waffle is good as well

Q's Benedict! So 🔥!  Chef Q is the man! His dishes are to die for. Not literally obviously but they are really good! He uses this spicy hollandaise sauce which is really unique and tasty. There are a ton of different hot sauces in this …
Fantastic eggs Benedict!
Very nice intimate place with great breakfast.

I had the loco moco and it was phenomenal. I also love the hole-in-the-wall concept, which makes the dining experience more intimate. All the workers seemed like they work very hard and act fast on each order.
A tiny place, but great food and great service.
I LOVE this place!! I come here every time I'm in town and get the Q Benedict. These guys know what they're doing. Best breakfast in Oakland
The food is an amazing blend of traditional American fare with Korean highlights. Only seats 10 inside and 8 outside when the weather is nice, so get there early!
A Korean fusion gem. Diverse brunch & spice bar. Small outdoor seating, perfect for parties of 2-4.  *Beef rice 🍚 & Qs Benedict $26
This chef is so humble and young, but so incredibly fantastic. The place is very small an original hole in the wall, but the food is so good.
Great breakfast, small and nicely crafted interior, sidewalk dining if you'd prefer and endless coffee refills. Perfect execution of a modern but classic breakfast diner
Very small and cozy restaurant, there was a 15 minute wait. As I waited I noticed that every plate was empty, No left overs. The food was delicious.

I keep forgetting about this cute little place. Which is a shame because the food is amazing. Diner fare with high flavor Korean punches. It appears family run so the space is very small and service is polite but not hurried. You always wanted bulgogi in your omelet didn't you?!

Delicious food in an ecleptic environment. It it's definitely a "cozy" restaurant has a small size, but small scale furniture makes it fit well. Staff is friendly, place was clean. A good place to eat. I would definitely consider eating there again if I happened to be in the area again.
Good food, but large portions. Was not expecting as much as I got. Too much one would even say
Cozy little place. Breakfast is awesome. Try Q's eggs benedict.

The man working here was extremely nice. A small little place with some indoor and outdoor seating. Had the best Eggs Benedict I have had in a long time called Q’s Benedict I believe. It was amazing. I wish I would have taken a picture to add here but I ate it so fast. Will absolutely be back. Fantastic service and food.
Loved the staff!

Super yummy Asian fusion food. Ordered a bulgogi omelette and a decked out French toast. They also have various Hawaiian food on the menu that I can’t wait to try another time. There are a few vegetarian options for my friend like eggs Benedict, but the meat dishes are definitely 🤤🤩
$5 burger!? 🍔 That’s da crazy. All of the dishes were lit. 🔥 Apparently they try out new dishes every 2-3 weeks. 👌 Korean fusion diner. Hole in the wall. Try it out before it blows up. 🍆💦
Great little place for breakfast!
Excellent food, great little spot.
Very Very nice people and the food aww man wooo you gotta come try their breakfast and even though it’s small its very cozy! Continue to make our tummy’s happy with that great food!!
Wonderful food and bring a friend 😁
Nice little breakfast place, excellent coffee.

I shouldn't even tell you about this place. But unfortunately they deserve to be known. Everything on the menu is delicious. The bulgogi with rice for breakfast is to die for. You have to bring your own chopsticks  though. And if you are in …

Small place. Very busy. Decent eggs benedict. Could've use more hollaindaise. Hashbrowns could've been crispier. Lots of hotsauce selction. Maybe they could use a helper om the weekends, I only saw a very overwhelmed girl taking orders.

Excellent food. The spicy pork is fantastic. Eggs over easy cooked to perfection. Price is reasonable for the quality and volume of food. One caveat: the restaurant appears to be a one man operation. It may not be the best food option if you are in a hurry.
Good food
Very good waffles, very friendly staff.

Small restaurant with great taste and friendly service! I tried the English muffin with beef and French Toast, it’s tasty and comforting your hungry stomach, ready to start the day! They cook your food one by one, fresh from the stove!

Really nice, but small. They clearly recently renovated the place. The coffee and service were good but the food was the best part (as it should be, right?). Absolutely delicious and reasonably priced.
Love this place  good food and nice atmosphere
Clean little jewel in Oakland... Great staff, great food....
Random cute quiet spot very small tho but  perfect!

A small and cosy place to have a nice breakfast. Recently renovated to have a more updated decor, this place can get crowded on the weekends. Plan to come early. I also understand that they will soon start opening on Sundays as well.
My girl not there anymore

I believe in upholding the basics when it comes to my breakfast sandwiches. And this place lives up to that. They have a good range of the standard breakfast sandwiches, proportions are fantastic- not too much meat, not too much bread or …
A hole in the wall near my dentist office.   Luv it. Small but very nice inside. Check it out!
Clean, friendly, solid breakfast place. I had eggs with grits and flavorful sausage patty.
Small spot, but great food and customer service.

Cash only! My favorite breakfast spot. Usual breakfast fare, reasonably priced and delicious. Tiny place with 4 or 5 tables and a few stools at the counter. Locals have frequented this place for decades, and I hope it'll stay for decades more.
Quick service and good coffee. Open earlier than most other places around here.
Wonderful hole in the wall without pretension.
Great neighborhood spot!
Perfect.
This place is awesome I've been coming here since I was a teen and stayed around the corner that was year's ago but every chance I get I come back for the teriyaki chicken and rice.
I've been eating at the Koffee Pot for 23 years since I was 13 years old & the food was excellent then & it is now. Congrats.

I love this place... I had been to many higher priced places for Teriyaki chicken. This place wins hand down. They also have good burgers and breakfast... Make sure you come early they walk out at 2:30 on the nose. Oh the place is small, more like a togo place. I will recommend this place to any and all.
